entry.title: [ios/SigninPromoViewMediator] Stop assuming kInstantSignin=Bookmarks/RL
entry.content:
No intended behavior change.

Before this CL, [SigninPromoViewMediator startInstantSignInFlow]

hardcoded a PostSignInAction::kEnableBookmarkReadingListAccountStorage

to pass to AuthenticationFlow. Regardless of self.accessPoint.



This CL moves the Bookmarks/RL opt-in to SigninPromoViewMediator -

conditioned to self.accessPoint - and converts the PostSignInAction to

kShowSnackbar, which is the common part to all entry points.



Alternatively, we could have kept the old PostSignInAction and passed

a new one depending on the accessPoint. But

a) That would push more complexity to AuthenticationFlow (extra states

and all).

b) The current approach leaves the code a little closer to the state

when kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos launches, and Bookmarks/RL

opt-in goes away.

entry.title: Don't pass events from dropped frames to adopter.
entry.content:
As per current logic the events from dropped frames are passed to

adopter, which is not fully correct. Let's take the example below:



| R1main |

| R1impl | R2impl | R3impl | R4impl |

| R2main |



The frame containing R1main and R2impl then any events it had would go

to R3impl and then R3impl gets adopted and R2main will get the events.

Any event latency metrics then will get computed when R2main finishes,

whereas the effects of events from R1main and R2impl would already have

been displayed in R3impl. After this change the metrics received from

dropped frames won't be passed to adopter and they get reported with

correct reporters.



Bug: b/289812788

entry.content:
Support for V4L2 decoders on standard Linux was recently added and

finished. Since this was previously only used by ChromeOS, which had

relaxed code style checking and other minor differences from the

standard Chrome builds, and V4L2 codecs aren't enabled by default

for Linux, ChromeOS work tends to overlook code style requirements

and other ChromeOS differences that may cause this support to

degrade again.

can be caught before they land.

entry.title: [exo] Update hit test and window resize for SetShape()
entry.content:
Currently the aura_toplevel.set_shape will set the layer shape of the

ShellSurface's host window.



However the resulting window does not correctly implement hit testing

for transparent regions created by the applied shape. The resulting

window also participates in server-side resize, which is disabled

for App windows using SetShape() in ash-chrome.



This CL instead applies the shape to the widget's layer as opposed to

the host window's layer. This is for correctness as the host window's

layer bounds can grow to accommodate all surfaces in the surface

hierarchy.



This CL also ensures correct hit testing by having the

CustomWindowTargeter of the shell surface take into account the

window's shape.



Server-side resize has also been disabled for windows using the

SetShape() API to match the current behavior on ash-chrome.



This CL also cleans up code, eliminating the need for shape rects

in many places.



Bug: 1158733, 1465999, b/286021229
